# CLAUDE.md

**Read `AGENTS.md` first — it is the operational source of truth for this repo.**

Everything an agent needs to work here lives in `AGENTS.md`: session start, AI
guidance, the Goal-loop work execution policy, the sandbox model, the technology
stack and command reference, the fast-tools/search conventions, and the session
completion protocol. That content is deliberately kept in one file rather than
mirrored here, because Codex reads `AGENTS.md` and does not read this file — a
copy here would drift and only one backend would notice.

This file exists so Claude Code, which loads `CLAUDE.md` automatically, is pointed
at the same instructions.

## Claude Code specifics

These apply only to the Claude Code backend; the Codex equivalents (where there
are any) are covered in `AGENTS.md`.

* Prefer `/compact` over letting the context window fill — a compaction loses less
  than an overflow. Re-run `bd prime` afterwards, per `AGENTS.md` § Session Start.
* Subagents are useful for wide read-only fan-out (searching many files for a
  symbol or convention). Keep the write path in the main session so the Goal loop's
  bookkeeping stays in one transcript.
* `.claude/settings.json` holds this project's permissions, hooks, and sandbox
  allowlist. `bd setup claude` installs the beads `SessionStart`/`PreCompact` hooks
  into it.
